interpreter

Class SQLInterpreter

  • java.lang.Object
    • interpreter.SQLInterpreter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DBInterpreter

    public class SQLInterpreter
extends java.lang.Object
implements DBInterpreter
    This class is a model interpreter based on getting database informations with DatabaseMetaData. Data is then processed: necessary tables, fields, relations and attributes are set.
    Author:
    Jelena, Nikola
    See Also:
    DatabaseMetaData

      • setParentChildRelations

        private void setParentChildRelations(DBSchema metaSchema)
        Setting up parent-child relations in Tables in metaSchema. If Table A references Table B and: (1) the referenced fields (foreign keys) match the primary keys of both A and B. (2) primary key of A contains the whole primary key of B, (3) where primary key of A can contain other elements as well then Table A is a child and Table B is parent.
        Parameters:
        metaSchema - DBSchema in which relations need to be set.
